    - ["ab3451008", operator.contains, [abc.ABCMeta.__dict__,                             "__delitem__"], false]
    - ["ab3451009", operator.contains, [type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)).__dict__,  "__delitem__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__ across all 3 abc subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 3 classes x 3 methods = 9 rows.
# __getitem__: false for all 3.
# __setitem__: false for all 3.
# __delitem__: false for all 3.
# All 9 values are false.
# Continues the all-false pattern from wave 676 (__le__/__gt__/__ge__).
# This wave re-examines dunders that were first tested individually in waves
#   656 (__getitem__) and 657 (__setitem__, __delitem__), confirming the results
#   are stable across the full wave run.
# The function type profile across all waves tested:
#   true:  __get__ (652), __repr__ (655), __call__ (656)
#   false: __set__, __delete__, __hash__, __eq__, __bool__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__,
#          __ge__, __str__, __len__, __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__,
#          __contains__, __add__, __sub__, __mul__, __truediv__, __floordiv__,
#          __mod__, __pow__, __lshift__, __rshift__, __and__, __or__, __xor__,
#          __radd__, __rsub__, __rmul__, __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__,
#          __rpow__, __rlshift__, __rrshift__, __rand__, __ror__, __rxor__,
#          __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__, __itruediv__, __ifloordiv__, __imod__,
#          __ipow__, __ilshift__, __irshift__, __iand__, __ior__, __ixor__,
#          __neg__, __pos__, __abs__, __invert__, __floor__, __ceil__,
#          __trunc__, __round__, __index__, __int__, __float__, __complex__,
#          __bool__ (674), __str__ (674), __repr__ (674),
#          __hash__ (675), __eq__ (675), __lt__ (675),
#          __le__ (676), __gt__ (676), __ge__ (676),
#          __getitem__ (677), __setitem__ (677), __delitem__ (677)
# The function type is tightly scoped to its role as a callable descriptor
#   with a display representation. Only __get__, __repr__, and __call__ are
#   true for the function type in its own __dict__.
# abc.ABCMeta note: ABCMeta has now returned false for every dunder tested
#   across 26 consecutive waves (652–677). Its power lies exclusively in
#   class-hierarchy machinery — not in operator overloading, comparison,
#   hashing, display, or container/mapping protocol overrides of any kind.
# abc.ABC note: ABC is a pure syntactic convenience for declaring abstract
#   base classes. It has no state of its own beyond what ABCMeta provides,
#   and defines no dunder of any kind in its own __dict__ across all tested
#   waves.
# Cross-wave summary for abc subjects:
#   Wave 652 (ab3076): __get__ true for function type; __set__/__delete__ false.
#   Wave 653 (ab3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ all false for all 3.
#   Wave 654 (ab3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ all false for all 3.
#   Wave 655 (ab3121): __ge__ false; __repr__ true for function type only; __str__ false.
#   Wave 656 (ab3136): __call__ true for function type only; __len__/__getitem__ false.
#   Wave 657 (ab3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 658 (ab3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 659 (ab3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 660 (ab3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 661 (ab3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 662 (ab3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 663 (ab3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 664 (ab3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 665 (ab3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 666 (ab3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 667 (ab3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 668 (ab3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 669 (ab3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 670 (ab3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 671 (ab3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 672 (ab3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 673 (ab3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 674 (ab3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 675 (ab3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 676 (ab3436): __le__/__gt__/__ge__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 677 (ab3451): __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ — all false for all 3.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

